:ITN042 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN042" ;
    :hasClinicalEffects "None specifically reported." ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Simultaneous administration of antacids had no effect on overall bioavailability but peak serum concentrations were reduced by approximately 24%." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Do not take azithromycin and antacids simultaneously" ;
    :hasReference :R039 ;
    :interactsWith :S022 .

:ITN043 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN043" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "In elderly patients concurrently receiving diuretics, mainly thiazide, there appears to be an increased risk of thrombocytopenia with purpura." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Use TMP-SMX with caution in elderly patients receiving thiazide diuretics" ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S031 .

:ITN044 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN044" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Occasionally reports suggest that patients receiving pyrimethamine as malarial prophylaxis in doses exceeding 25 mg weekly may develop megaloblastic anaemia if Co- trimoxazole be prescribed concurrently." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Avoid combination or closely monitor CBC for megaloblastic anemia." ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S032 .

:ITN045 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN045" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Cotrimoxazole has been shown to potentiate activity of strongly serum protein-bound drugs like oral hypoglycaemic or anticoagulant." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor for enhanced drug effects and adjust doses as needed." ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S033 .

:ITN046 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN046" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "It has been reported that comazole may displace the anticoagulant warfarin. Careful control of the anticoagulant therapy during treatment with Comazole is advisable." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor INR closely and reduce warfarin dose if necessary." ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S034 .

:ITN047 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN047" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Comazole also may inhibit the hepatic metabolism of phenytoin. A 39% increase in phenytoin half-life and 27% decrease in the metabolic clearance rate of phenytoin have been observed following administration of Comazole of normal clinical dosages. If these two drugs are given concurrently it is important to remain alert for signs of phenytoin toxicity." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor serum phenytoin levels and signs of toxicity. Dose adjustment may be required." ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S035 .

:ITN048 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN048" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Concurrent use of rifampicin and Comazole results in shortening of plasma half life of trimethoprim." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor clinical response as trimethoprim levels may be reduced. Consider alternative therapy." ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S036 .

:ITN049 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN049" ;
    :hasClinicalEffects "None specifically reported in the dedicated drug interaction study." ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Concurrent use of warfarin and azithromycin may potentiate the effects of oral anticoagulants." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Prothrombin time should be carefully monitored while patients are receiving azithromycin and oral anticoagulants concurrently" ;
    :hasReference :R038 ;
    :interactsWith :S018 .

:ITN050 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN050" ;
    :hasClinicalEffects "Dose adjustment of azithromycin is not recommended when administered in combination with nelfinavir." ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "Co-administration with a single oral dose of azithromycin resulted in increased azithromycin serum concetration." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Close monitoring for known adverse effects of azithromycin, such as liver enzyme abnormalities and hearing impairment." ;
    :hasReference :R038 ;
    :interactsWith :S037 .

:ITN054 a :Interaction ;
    rdfs:label "ITN054" ;
    :hasInteractionDescription "In elderly patients concurrently receiving diuretics, mainly thiazide, there appears to be an increased risk of thrombocytopenia with purpura." ;
    :hasManagementAdvice "Use TMP-SMX with caution in elderly patients receiving thiazide diuretics" ;
    :hasReference :R031 ;
    :interactsWith :S031 .

