    :hasPattern :Early_in_treatment ;
    :hasReference :R157 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "A sick feeling in the stomach that may make the patient feel like vomiting. It usually improves when the medicine is taken with food." .

:SE516 a :Vomiting ;
    rdfs:label "Vomiting" ;
    :hasDurationOf "Short-term" ;
    :hasPattern :Early_in_treatment ;
    :hasReference :R157 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "Forceful emptying of stomach contents. It may happen if the medicine irritates the stomach. Taking the capsule with meals may reduce this effect." .

:SE517 a :LossOfAppetite ;
    rdfs:label "Loss of Appetite" ;
    :hasDurationOf "Short-term" ;
    :hasPattern :During_therapy ;
    :hasReference :R158 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "Decreased desire to eat. The patient may feel full quickly or uninterested in food while taking the medicine." .

:SE518 a :Headache ;
    rdfs:label "Headache" ;
    :hasDurationOf "Short-term" ;
    :hasPattern :Occasional_during_use ;
    :hasReference :R158 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "Mild to moderate head pain that may feel like pressure or throbbing. Usually resolves after the body adjust to the medicine." .

:SE519 a :UrineColorChange ;
    rdfs:label "Urine Color" ;
    :hasDurationOf "While taking the drug" ;
    :hasPattern :Very_common ;
    :hasReference :R157 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "The urine may turn dark yellow or brown in color. This is harmless and happens because the drug is being removed through the urine. It is not sign of kidney damage." .

:SE520 a :LungReaction ;
    rdfs:label "Lung Reaction" ;
    :hasDurationOf "Can be sudden or develop with long-term use" ;
    :hasPattern :Rare_but_serious ;
    :hasReference :R159 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "May cause cough, chest pain, fever, and difficulty breathing. Acute reactions can happen suddenly within days, while chronic reactions may develop after long-term use. Medical attention is needed immediately." .

:SE521 a :PeripheralNeuropathy ;
    rdfs:label "Peripheral Neuropathy" ;
    :hasDurationOf "May last if not treated early" ;
    :hasPattern :Rare__higher_risk_in_kidney_disease ;
    :hasReference :R158 ;
    :hasSideEffectDescription "Damage to nerves that may cause numbness, tingling, burning, or weakness in the hands and feet. Risk is higher in patients with kidney problems or long-term use." .

