:SP143 a :AdministrationAndAdherence ;
    rdfs:label "SP143" ;
    :hasReference :R092 ;
    :hasStewardshipDescription "In the event of acute overdosage, reversible renal toxicity has been reported in some cases. It is recommended to monitor renal function and to administer magnesium- or calcium-containing antacids which reduce the absorption of ciprofloxacin." .

:SP144 a :AdministrationAndAdherence ;
    rdfs:label "SP144" ;
    :hasReference :R092 ;
    :hasStewardshipDescription "In the event of acute overdosage, reversible renal toxicity has been reported in some cases. It is recommended to monitor renal function and to administer magnesium- or calcium-containing antacids which reduce the absorption of ciprofloxacin." .

:SP145 a :FoodAndTiming ;
    rdfs:label "SP145" ;
    :hasReference :R091 ;
    :hasStewardshipDescription "Do not use Ciprofloxacin simulataneously with antacid preparations containing Magnesium Hydroxide or Aluminum Hydrocide. An interval of at least 2 hours must be respected between the administration of an antacid and Ciprofloxacin." .

:SP146 a :TherapeuticUseAndMonitoring ;
    rdfs:label "SP146" ;
    :hasReference :R091 ;
    :hasStewardshipDescription "Patients receiving Ciprofloxacin must be well hydrated to prevent crystalluria. Excessive alkalinisation of urine should be avoided." .

:SP147 a :TherapeuticUseAndMonitoring ;
    rdfs:label "SP147" ;
    :hasReference :R092 ;
    :hasStewardshipDescription "Avoid excessive sunlight" .

:SP148 a :TherapeuticUseAndMonitoring ;
